    "originating_user_signal": "PO 2026-05-24 during catalogs-of-pictures planning conversation: 'all of those other things were done prior to me developing OAGP, which is why the artifacts are scattered. In fact, Thingalog *led* to OAGP, which started out as the idea \"Hmmmm.... an organization is nothing more than a catalog of positions\".' Followed by directive 'First, file the OAGP memo' — explicit cross-org filing request.",
    "key_observations_for_canonical_consideration": [
      "catdef at substrate-stack root has HISTORICAL grounding, not just architectural convenience. Provenance is: collectables → pxcatalog → Thingalog → OAGP. Treating catdef as 'the layer the substrate started from' is historically accurate.",
      "Thingalog is OAGP's empirical anchor and dogfood. When Thingalog needs a primitive that catdef doesn't currently support cleanly (audio attachment field type, field-level history, recursive table fields / Values-with-Fields), that's signal for catdef-canonical revision, not signal that Thingalog should work around catdef.",
      "Pre-OAGP artifacts in pxlegacy/ are NOT candidates for absorption into OAGP-canonical structure. They predate OAGP. They're prior-art for Thingalog. Treat as inheritance, not as integration backlog.",
      "PXMemories' PRODUCT.md articulates several patterns that are now Thingalog/OAGP doctrine: AI-as-named-companion (precedes 'AI as peer' orgdef v1.3.0 by months), graph-as-memory ('the graph is the truth, EXIF is the postcard'), per-tenant family-scale catalogs, lifetime data ownership ('Not lock-in. Love.'), inactivity-triggered pricing. These doctrinal alignments were independent convergence, not coordination — strong evidence that the substrate is reaching toward something stable.",
      "The Recursive Table Fields pattern in pxlegacy/THINGALOG.md (Values-with-sub-Fields, e.g., 'Watch Complications') is in Scott's own founding Thingalog strategy doc but has not shipped to current Thingalog. It is the natural data-shape primitive for things like 'a Person value carrying birth_year, death_year, married_name, photo, GEDCOM_ref' — which PXMemories needs. Catdef revision candidate to surface when staffed."
    ],
